notes.en: A lo-fi jazz foundry for city girls and boys, located in Euljiro (referred to as Hipjiro). The venue, named 'ê¸°ì›' (Giwon), carries the double meaning of 'origin' and a place for playing Go (Baduk), reflecting its past as a Go club 30 years ago. It is run by Kang Woong, a jazz record producer and musician. Giwon offers jazz music chosen by the owner's taste, primarily modern jazz played on vinyl during weekdays, paired with a curated selection of natural wines (80% of the wine list). Live performances by jazz musicians are held every Saturday, with booking exclusively available via Instagram DM. Performance schedules are announced one week in advance on Instagram, or a month in advance for those who visit in person. The owner is a record collector and also allows fellow DJs or musicians to select music.
